def: A North American aquatic fur-bearing rodent (Fiber zibethicus).It resembles a rat in color and having a long scaly tail, but thetail is compressed, the bind feet are webbed, and the ears areconcealed in the fur. It has scent glands which secrete a substancehaving a strong odor of musk. Called also musquash, musk beaver, andondatra.
In a heap; huddled together. Hood.
A noun that has four cases only. Andrews.
The condition or quality of being general; frequency;commonness. Sir P. Sidney.
A Linnean genus of mollusks having a conical shell. See Cone,n., 4.

Mutual discourse or conversation; discussion; hence, an oralconference with an enemy, as with regard to a truce.We yield on parley, but are stormed in vain. Dryden.To beat a parley (Mil.), to beat a drum, or sound a trumpet, as asignal for holding a conference with the enemy.
Not Episcopal; not pertaining to the Episcopal church orsystem.
A place or ground set apart for the burial of the dead; agraveyard; a churchyard; a necropolis.
